<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="10" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/665: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-05T10:00:00-05:00">February 5, 1930—10
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>55. The suggestions contained in your telegram No. 35, February 4, have
                            been considered and are heartily approved by the President.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
